subSubSection.paragraph:
characterized by a massive body, large and blunt head, spiny fur, small eyes, and tail same or longer than head-body length. External differences between Ruschi’s Spiny Mouse and Chebez’s Spiny Mouse (A. 
chebezi
) are subtle; Ruschi’s Spiny Mouse is larger than Chebez’s Spiny Mouse and typically has white terminal tuft on tail; it is brown dorsally and yellowish to whitish ventrally.
